                  <interp inst="t18180617-16-crimeloc87" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180617-16-off84 t18180617-16-crimeloc87"></join>, the prisoner was our <rs id="t18180617-16-deflabel88" type="occupation">errand-boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180617-16-defend161 t18180617-16-deflabel88"></join>. On Saturday evening, the 6th of June, about seven o'clock, I put the 1l. note, with others, in a drawer in a private room<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="181806170009"></xptr> - I returned home about half-past ten and missed it. I had just sent him home. I went to his father's, and found he had not got home. I found him under the Piazza in Covent-garden, just as the Theatre was over, and charged him with taking the note, which he denied several times - I took him to the watch-house. On searching him, he gave up 15s., which he said was part of it, and said he was very sorry for having taken it. It was No. 56,456.</p>
               <p>
            
